\
The positive snow and ice albedo feedback can amplify a cooling, as well as a warming. If the climate cools, the resulting increased snow and ice cover reflects more sunlight back to space, and the cooling is amplified. <i>Note that both positive and negative feedbacks can cause either warming or cooling; their role is to amplify or damp a temperature change.</i>\
